<HEADLINE>
FT  05 MAY 93 / UK Company News: Somerset Trust shares suspended
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in Somerset Trust, formerly known as the Children's Medical Charity
Investment Trust, were suspended yesterday morning at 178p at the request of
the company, which later announced that it was in talks which might lead to
a substantial acquisition.
The potential acquisition is a manufacturing company with turnover of about
Pounds 20m. If the acquisition proceeds it will constitute a reverse
takeover of Somerset.
The consideration of some Pounds 19m will be funded by a placing and rights
issue. The company expects to make a further announcement in the next three
to four weeks.
The trust currently holds the bulk of its funds in short-dated gilts. Last
September, it reported a rise in net asset value to 86.2p per share as at
June 30, against 82.6p six months earlier.
</TEXT>
