<HEADLINE>
FT  05 MAY 93 / UK Company News: Saatchi makes Dollars 14.8m disposal
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Saatchi &amp; Saatchi is raising about Dollars 14.8m (Pounds 9.6m) from the sale
of the Howard Marlboro Group, which comprises three companies engaged in
various forms of in-store marketing.
The companies are being sold to MarkitStar, a US group whose shares are
traded on Nasdaq.
The companies - Marlboro Marketing, Creative Displays and HMG Europe - are
all indirectly wholly owned subsidiaries of Saatchi and operate in New York,
Chicago and the Netherlands respectively.
Their preliminary results for 1992 indicate turnover of Pounds 37.1m,
pre-tax losses of Pounds 500,000 and net tangible assets of Pounds 5m at the
year end.
