FT  05 MAY 93 / UK Company News: Ingham makes recovery to Pounds 452,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
INGHAM, the worsted spinner and retailer of new parts for British classic
sports cars, returned pre-tax profits of Pounds 452,000 for the 12 months to
end-December.
The year-end has been changed to March 31 and the outcome compared with
losses of Pounds 152,000 for the corresponding 12 months.
Last month, when Ingham gave details of the proposed acquisition of Moss
Europe and an accompanying rights issue, shareholders were told that the
figures in the second interim statement would be meaningless for purposes of
comparison.
They included the results of Transtar for three months only; the period
coincided with Transtar's traditionally quietist trading period.
Ingham's earnings emerged at 6.1p (losses 4.7p). Payment of a 1.25p final
dividend has been brought forward for a total of 7.25p (3p for the 12 months
to December 31 1991).
