FT  05 MAY 93 / BT cuts phone link charges
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN CANE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITISH Telecommunications yesterday announced cuts in the cost of line
connection for both business and domestic customers, Alan Cane writes. The
changes bring the cost of installing the first telephone for a business with
a single line down to Pounds 116.33, including value added tax, from Pounds
179.49.
The corresponding reduction for home lines is from Pounds 163.75 to Pounds
116.33. The cuts will be effective from June 1 this year. The new prices are
part of BT's compliance with its agreement with Oftel, the
telecommunications regulator, to keep price changes on a range of services
to 6.25 percentage points below the rate of inflation.
