FT  05 MAY 93 / Four new ministers in Italian cabinet
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GRAHAM
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Carlo Azeglio Ciampi, Italy's prime minister, yesterday named four new
ministers in his cabinet, writes Robert Graham. They replace ministers
withdrawn by their parties in protest at the blocking by parliament of
attempts to have Mr Bettino Craxi, the former Socialist leader, answer
corruption charges.
The environment portfolio, vacated by the Greens, was given to Mr Valdo
Spini, a Socialist deputy who briefly held the same post in the outgoing
Amato government.
The posts of finance, science and relations with parliament, held by members
of the former communist Party of the Democratic Left (PDS), went
respectively to Prof Franco Gallo, an economist, Prof Umberto Colombo, a
distinguished scientist and head of the research institute Enea, and Prof
Paolo Barile, who has switched from minister without portfolio. Mr Livio
Paladin, a judge and former minister of regional affairs, is to be put in
charge of relations with the European Community.
