<HEADLINE>
FT  04 MAY 93 / Observer: Going for broke
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
So chancellor Norman Lamont was right all along - those green shoots were
stirring even in the depths of recession.
The latest retailer profitability rankings, drawn up by market research firm
Corporate Intelligence, show Harvey &amp; Thompson, Britain's 581st largest
retailer - since last year trading as Lightship - firmly at the head of the
league table achieving an extravagant 46.4 per cent pre-tax margin on sales
in 1990-91. Its business? A pawnbroker.
