FT  04 MAY 93 / People: National Association of Probation Officers
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Joining the tiny band - now three - of female trade union general
secretaries from today is Judy McKnight, who becomes leader of the
7,000-strong National Association of Probation Officers. She succeeds Bill
Beaumont who did the job for seven years.
McKnight has made her career in public sector unions; her last job was as
assistant general secretary at the National Union of Civil and Public
Servants. Before that, she worked for the Civil and Public Service
Association.
